48:29.673 --> 48:31.133
Move back, I am the Sheriff.

48:41.643 --> 48:47.210
Ok, Cinema Club, we re not in session. Welcome.
I'll tell you a little bit about ourselves.

48:47.210 --> 48:54.196
We re a sanctioned after school activity, one rung
below the Glee club, two above Nintendo Wii Fit

48:54.196 --> 48:59.795
and let me just say to our guest
, Sidney Prescott, it's an honor.

49:03.308 --> 49:07.416
Beyond Jamie Lee Curtis, forget Linda
Blair, I mean, this is the ultimate.

49:07.905 --> 49:14.725
Thanks, I-I guess. This, uhm... you film your entire High
School experience and what, post it on the net?

49:14.725 --> 49:18.760
- Everybody will be doing it someday, Sid.
- It's kind of the one component the killer is missing.

49:18.760 --> 49:20.360
- Wait, what do you mean?

49:20.400 --> 49:25.756
- Well, if you wanna be the new "new version",
the killer should be filming the murders.

49:25.756 --> 49:30.103
That's like the natural next step in the psycho slasher
innovation. I mean you film em all real time

49:30.103 --> 49:32.960
- and then before you get caught,
you upload em into cyberspace.

49:33.000 --> 49:34.659
- Making your art as immortal as you.

49:35.702 --> 49:37.194
- Not to implicate him...
- Not to implicate me...

49:37.506 --> 49:43.250
- So who do you think is behind the murders?
- Well, it's a Stab fanatic, clearly.

49:43.563 --> 49:45.880
Working on less of a Screquel
and more of a Screamake.

49:45.920 --> 49:47.285
- Copyrighted terms, by the way.

49:47.285 --> 49:50.934
Cos all there are now are remakes.
Only horror the studios green-light.

49:51.247 --> 49:55.908
I mean, there are still rules, but the rules have
changed. The unexpected is the new clichÃ©.

49:55.908 --> 49:58.764
Yeah, you gotta have an opening sequence
that blows the doors off

49:58.764 --> 50:02.873
done with some flashy music video direction.
And the kills gotta be way more extreme.

50:02.873 --> 50:07.845
Modern audiences got savvy to the rules of the originals,
so the reversals become the new standard.

50:07.845 --> 50:13.308
In fact, the only surefire way to survive a modern
horror movie, you pretty much have to be gay.

50:16.260 --> 50:20.080
So, why are you so sure that the killer is
working by the rules of a horror remake?

50:20.120 --> 50:22.661
- Well, the original Stab structure is pretty apparent.

50:22.661 --> 50:25.080
- Two kids killed in a house while
their parents are away.

50:25.120 --> 50:27.708
- And then the school's "hot chick"
savaged beyond recognition.

50:27.708 --> 50:30.209
- We all know where it goes from there...
- A party.

50:30.877 --> 50:34.800
- Exactly. A party. Guaranteed
third act main cast blood bath.

50:34.840 --> 50:37.727
- Fingers crossed on some nudity for a change.

50:40.094 --> 50:44.890
- Ok, do you know of a party that's happening tonight?
- Well, there's Stab- a- thon.

50:46.109 --> 50:47.200
- Stab- a- thon?

50:47.240 --> 50:51.990
- Uh, It's a movie marathon. All 7 Stabs
back to back. We do it every year.

50:51.990 --> 50:57.360
- Is tonight? There's a killer out there patterning
his murders after the original movie.

50:57.400 --> 50:59.090
- I know, it's pretty wild.

50:59.090 --> 51:00.414
We have to call it off.

51:00.758 --> 51:05.732
- Uhm, ok, I mean, it's Friday. I am sure we re not
the only party that's going on at Woodsboro.

51:05.732 --> 51:10.183
- But where is this circle-jerk gonna take place?
- So, let's ready for this Q&A.

51:10.183 --> 51:12.120
- No, no. I really want the location.

51:12.160 --> 51:16.138
- You know, it's kind of an underground
thing. Email invites. Pretty secret.

51:17.149 --> 51:23.331
What, you re not gonna tell me? Really?
We re working together. Remember?

51:24.696 --> 51:27.856
- So you re ready for the Q&A?
- Fuck you. Let's go.

51:32.172 --> 51:33.392
That was awesome.

51:34.017 --> 51:36.801
- Nobody comes to the house unless we say so.
- Got it.

51:36.801 --> 51:38.886
I feel like I'm under house arrest.

51:54.265 --> 51:59.640
You know when people say "I know how
you feel", but you know they re just saying

51:59.680 --> 52:01.918
that because they really have no

52:01.918 --> 52:08.246
freaking idea how you feel? I know how you feel.

52:12.177 --> 52:14.679
I am so sorry about Olivia.

52:19.622 --> 52:21.467
I am sorry about your publicist.

52:26.617 --> 52:31.520
How do you handle it, people
staring at you all the time?

52:31.560 --> 52:33.436
- People stare at me?

