56:14.657 --> 56:15.700
Screw you!

56:51.951 --> 56:52.952
Yes!

56:59.979 --> 57:02.106
Uh, Yeah. Back on my game.

57:04.014 --> 57:07.257
Perfect. New work in progress, chapter 1.

57:07.601 --> 57:14.316
When I moved to Woodsboro, I never in a million years
dreamed that I would again play the critical role...

57:14.316 --> 57:16.890
...in solving another series of these...

57:25.553 --> 57:26.702
What the hell?

57:50.254 --> 57:53.872
- Gale, where are you?
- I followed the kids to the Stab-a-thon.

57:54.154 --> 57:58.640
There's an old abandoned farm on 4th Dylan Road.
Listen, I-I got it under surveillance, but

57:58.680 --> 58:00.898
I think the killer is about to make his move.

58:01.451 --> 58:03.080
- What makes you so sure?

58:03.120 --> 58:07.373
- You do a remake to outdo the original,
that's what the kids said.

58:07.373 --> 58:11.753
This party is all about the Stab movies.
Come on, how meta can you get?

58:12.243 --> 58:15.860
- How "what the.." can you get?
- I dunno, I heard em say it.

58:16.278 --> 58:22.637
- Dewey, listen to me, you have to get out here. Come
on, you catch the killer, I get the story. It's a win-win.

58:22.637 --> 58:27.474
- Well, I thought you were going rogue, Gale.
- Oh come..are you serious? C'mon!

58:28.560 --> 58:33.800
- Forget it. Thanks for having faith
in me! I gotta fix my equipment.

58:33.840 --> 58:34.502
- Gale!

58:37.317 --> 58:38.328
Shit.

58:53.468 --> 59:00.421
Bravo, well... very well done, very, I'm very impressed.
Kind of. Kinda impressed. Not Really.

59:00.807 --> 59:02.611
- That'll do. - Yeah? - Yeah.

59:02.611 --> 59:04.977
- Yeah, she wants you.
- Yeah. Yeah.

59:07.793 --> 59:10.369
<i>Nooooooo!</i>

59:12.808 --> 59:13.642
<i>Ghostface.....</i>

59:22.785 --> 59:25.089
<i>- Hello?</i>
<i>- Hello.</i>

59:26.090 --> 59:30.124
<i>- Who is this?</i>
<i>- Were you expecting somebody now?</i>

59:37.465 --> 59:40.947
<i>You know, I don't even know you...</i>
<i>- ...and I dislike you already.</i>

59:41.260 --> 59:45.129
- Hicks, how far are you from 4th Dylan Road?
- 5 minutes at the most, Sir.

59:45.129 --> 59:45.890
Well, step on it.

59:48.287 --> 59:49.538
<i>Look out your window.</i>

01:00:35.008 --> 01:00:37.343
Gale! Gale, behind you!

01:00:49.655 --> 01:00:50.208
No!

01:00:54.212 --> 01:00:55.046
Gale!

01:01:10.602 --> 01:01:11.436
Freeze!

01:01:25.209 --> 01:01:26.814
Get out of the way, you morons!

01:01:32.339 --> 01:01:33.246
Dammit.

01:01:36.793 --> 01:01:39.962
- Ok, put pressure on that.
- Did you catch him?

01:01:39.962 --> 01:01:45.216
- No, hopefully your cameras got something.
- They weren't the only ones, Dewey.

01:01:45.216 --> 01:01:48.480
- What?
- There's a webcam... set back there.

01:01:48.480 --> 01:01:51.305
- He was watching me.
- A webcam?

01:01:51.753 --> 01:01:54.328
- He's recording the murders.
- What?

01:01:54.850 --> 01:01:58.228
This time... he's making the movie.

01:02:02.816 --> 01:02:07.028
This Sidney Prescott detail man, I don't like it.

01:02:07.757 --> 01:02:09.874
The cops scouting the house, they always get it.

01:02:11.240 --> 01:02:13.773
What are you talking about?
- It's a movie cop rule.

01:02:14.190 --> 01:02:17.880
Sucks to be a cop in a movie.
Unless you re Bruce Willis.

01:02:17.920 --> 01:02:19.831
- Not all cops die in movies.

01:02:20.457 --> 01:02:24.002
No, but if it's your last day before retirement you do.

01:02:24.805 --> 01:02:27.588
If you re a rookie, some with a
wife who's pregnant, you do.

01:02:29.121 --> 01:02:33.218
Or if your partner is better looking than you,
you do, and by the way, I win that one.

01:02:35.417 --> 01:02:38.234
You know what, I'll take the next perimeter. I'll be right back.

01:02:40.600 --> 01:02:41.393
Shit.

01:02:41.393 --> 01:02:44.840
- I know this one, you re not supposed
to say that, are you?

01:02:44.880 --> 01:02:46.480
- Eh, new decade, new rules.

01:02:46.480 --> 01:02:50.720
You know, these days, you might come
back, find me dead. Eyes gouged out, tongue

01:02:50.760 --> 01:02:52.600
sticking out. Could go either way.

01:02:52.600 --> 01:02:56.322
- I gotta learn this shit.
- Eh, I'll take this one.

01:02:58.752 --> 01:03:03.944
- Hey, Hoss. Be careful.
- I am always careful.

01:03:07.874 --> 01:03:09.542
Dead man walking.

01:03:59.807 --> 01:04:07.220
- Perkins, was there a window open on your last
perimeter check? Perkins, come in. Over.

01:04:38.247 --> 01:04:38.737
Anthony?

01:04:41.033 --> 01:04:41.554
Perkins?

01:04:47.225 --> 01:04:51.093
- Dammit.
- You should have seen the look on your face, rookie.

01:04:53.418 --> 01:04:55.441
Hoss! What the fuck!

01:04:57.557 --> 01:04:58.599
Holy shit...

01:05:09.349 --> 01:05:10.152
Hoss!

01:05:27.198 --> 01:05:28.345
Fuck Bruce Willis!

01:05:57.601 --> 01:06:02.992
- Sorry. The wind chimes were over here.
- It was me, I was trying to fix em, sorry.

01:06:04.879 --> 01:06:07.934
- I am just back the store.
- Were you shopping?

01:06:08.247 --> 01:06:12.385
A stress buster. I got one more bag
in the car. I'll be right back.

01:06:38.721 --> 01:06:40.118
Jill, you re gonna get that?

01:06:44.530 --> 01:06:47.803
<i>- Roberts residence.</i>
<i>- You re a survivor, aren't you, Sidney?</i>

01:06:47.803 --> 01:06:53.193
<i>Your one and only skill: You survive.</i>
<i>Well, I have one question for you.</i>

01:06:53.818 --> 01:06:58.375
<i>What good did to be a survivor in this little</i>
drama if everyone close to you is dead?

01:06:58.896 --> 01:07:01.888
<i>- Who are you?</i>
<i>- Turn on the TV to channel 6.</i>

01:07:01.888 --> 01:07:05.340
<i>- Who the fuck are you?</i>
<i>- Turn it on. Watch the teaser.</i>

01:07:07.247 --> 01:07:11.360
...But it nearly turned deadly tonight, with
the latest victim of this attack being

01:07:11.400 --> 01:07:13.232
the wife of the Woodsboro Sheriff...

01:07:13.232 --> 01:07:18.400
...Gale Riley, AKA Gale Weathers, who's in
serious condition tonight after being stabbed.

01:07:18.440 --> 01:07:20.437
Her assailant then disappeared...

01:07:20.437 --> 01:07:25.515
<i>in a sea of identic.... - Glad you came home,</i>
Sidney. Has it been worth it yet?

01:07:25.515 --> 01:07:27.360
- Why are you doing this?

01:07:27.400 --> 01:07:32.572
- Ah, friends count, but it's the family
ties that cut deep. Am I right?

01:07:33.240 --> 01:07:34.560
- What do you mean?

01:07:34.600 --> 01:07:38.870
- The ones you care about most.
And what's closer than family?

01:07:38.870 --> 01:07:40.715
<i>- The bond of blood.</i>
<i>- Don't.</i>

01:07:41.205 --> 01:07:45.137
<i>You can't save them. All you can do is watch.</i>

01:07:46.596 --> 01:07:47.357
Jill!

01:08:06.187 --> 01:08:07.917
- Kate!
- Sid?

01:08:07.917 --> 01:08:09.940
- She's not in her room.
- Oh my God.

01:08:09.940 --> 01:08:11.920
