phone? I think I left it in your car, I didn't text him.

01:12:47.618 --> 01:12:51.381
I didn't text you. And I'll prove it!

01:12:53.289 --> 01:12:58.472
So, Charlie, Robbie, how does it feel
to be accessories to a crime, huh?

01:12:58.858 --> 01:13:02.475
- I mean, really? Dewey's wife?
- My life is over.

01:13:02.684 --> 01:13:05.436
So which one of you guys sent me a
text message from Jill's phone, huh?

01:13:08.220 --> 01:13:11.640
- W-We re just supposed to accept
that you re telling the truth?

01:13:11.680 --> 01:13:13.151
- Isn't your phone missing?

01:13:14.371 --> 01:13:18.542
- Got a new one.
- Really? Oh, that's incredibly convenient.

01:13:20.430 --> 01:13:22.275
Dewey, it's Hicks.
- What's up?

01:13:23.380 --> 01:13:24.985
- Kate Roberts is dead.
- Huh?

01:13:24.985 --> 01:13:29.124
- And Sidney fled the scene.
- What, what happened to Kate?

01:13:29.645 --> 01:13:32.284
- She was stabbed, just like the others.
- And what about Jill?

01:13:32.711 --> 01:13:36.256
- No sign of her at all
- Where the hell were Hoss and Perkins?

01:13:36.882 --> 01:13:42.199
<i>They were found dead in their car two</i>
<i>blocks away. Multiple stab wounds.</i>

01:13:43.210 --> 01:13:47.871
<i>Ok. I'm on my way.</i>
<i>- Yes, Sir.</i>

01:13:55.773 --> 01:13:58.454
<i>- Wrong number.</i>
<i>- Who was that?</i>

